snippet: In an outpouring of rage against President Mohamed Morsi, a core of protesters set fire to the headquarters of Mr. Morsi’s Muslim Brotherhood movement in Cairo.
abstract: Millions of Egyptians flood streets of cities across country, demanding ouster of Pres Mohamed Morsi, in outpouring of anger at political dominance of his Islamist backers in Muslim Brotherhood; numbers exceed even those in 2011 demonstrations that lead to overthrow of Pres Hosni Mubarak; at least seven die and hundreds are injured in clashes between protesters and Morsi's supporters.

byline.original: By DAVID D. KIRKPATRICK, KAREEM FAHIM and BEN HUBBARD

lead_paragraph: In an outpouring of rage against President Mohamed Morsi, a core of protesters set fire to the headquarters of Mr. Morsi’s Muslim Brotherhood movement in Cairo.
